    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (1997) - SECTION 3.5: CIRCUIT FUNCTION AND DIAGNOSTICS - INJECTOR DRIVE
        MODULE (IDM) POWER SUPPLY - FAULT DETECTION MANAGEMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FAULT DETECTION MANAGEMENT</title>
        <para>The IDM power circuits are not continuously monitored. If the circuit is not operating the engine will not
            run. The ECM uses the Output Circuit Check (OCC) initiated during a Standard Test to test the IDM relay
            control coil circuits for opens or shorts (high and low).
        </para>
        <para>On each power up the IDM performs a self check. If internal faults are detected, a fault code will be set
            during an Engine Standard Test.
        </para>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="ef12518111">3.118</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            and
            <emph type="bold">Table 19</emph>
            for the circuit diagram and table for the injector drive module power supply.
        </para>
        <figure id="ef12518111" figsize="col-wide">
